<!-- page 1 -->
	<string id="p1text1"> You know that there are 26 letters in the English language.</string>
	<string id="p1text2"> We are going to focus on five special letters.</string>
	<string id="p1text3">These five letters are called #vowels@. </string>
	<string id="p1text4">Vowels are special because they change the way other letters sound in words.
</string>
	<string id="p1text5">Sometimes vowels make short sounds. &lt;br&gt;
Sometimes vowels make  long sounds.
</string>
	<string id="p1text6">In this lesson, we are going to look at
                                 the short vowel sounds.
</string>
	<string id="p1text7"></string>
<!--page 1 end-->


